      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bigger Threat to Earth</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Updating Prescriptions for Avoiding Worldwide Catastrophe'' (Conversation, Sept. 12), the scientist James Lovelock makes the absurd claim that ''even the results of an all-out nuclear war pale into insignificance as unimportant compared to what's going to happen'' with global warming. Rather, the nuclear winter after such a war would lead to mass starvation, killing most of the world's population.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Updating Prescriptions for Avoiding Worldwide Catastrophe'' (Conversation, Sept. 12), the scientist James Lovelock makes the absurd claim that ''even the results of an all-out nuclear war pale into insignificance as unimportant compared to what's going to happen'' with global warming. Rather, the nuclear winter after such a war would lead to mass starvation, killing most of the world's population.</p>
        <p>Gradual global warming is a serious threat, but the climatic effects of nuclear war would be much worse, and are the greatest potential environmental danger to our civilization.</p>
        <p>Alan Robock  New Brunswick, N.J.</p>
      </block>
